Project Overview

This project implements a wireless remote-controlled car using an ESP32 microcontroller. The vehicle uses two 12 V 200 RPM DC motors placed diagonally for differential steering. Motor control is handled by two L298N motor drivers, while a buck converter regulates voltage for the ESP32.

The ESP32 receives commands from a mobile device and translates them into motor driver signals to control forward, reverse, left, and right motion.

The goal of this project was to explore:

ESP32 wireless control

Motor driver interfacing

Power management with buck converters

Differential steering control
